('5918', '1', 'Combine the ingredients and set aside in container. This step can be done the day before dinner.'),
('5918', '2', 'Peel and cut the citrus fruit into sections over a plate.'),
('5918', '3', 'Drain the juice from the plate into a bowl. Season liberally with gray salt and black pepper.'),
('5918', '4', 'Whisk in olive oil to form a vinaigrette (it should be in proportion, about 2 parts juice to 1 part olive oil).'),
('5918', '5', 'Season citrus sections with salt and pepper.'),
('5918', '6', 'Drizzle a little of the vinaigrette on them to marinate and put them on a platter.'),
('5918', '7', 'Have your fishmonger peel the prawns but leave the tails on for handles. Season liberally with salt and pepper. Preheat a saute pan on high. Dredge the shrimp in the flour mixture. This will give them a nice crust and allow them to stay crispy and fresh at room temperature.'),
('5918', '8', 'Add olive oil to the pan and put in 1 layer of shrimp. You want them to caramelize, so don''t toss or move them.'),
('5918', '9', 'Add a little more oil if the flour absorbs what''s in the pan. After about 3 minutes, turn over the prawns.'),
('5918', '10', 'Let it caramelize, toss and turn out onto a cookie sheet.'),
('5918', '11', 'Add about 1/4 cup more olive oil to the already hot saute pan.'),
('5918', '12', 'Drain pan juices from the cookie sheet into the saute pan.'),
('5918', '13', 'Add sliced garlic and let it get light brown.'),
('5918', '14', 'Add chiles and let them get soft.'),
('5918', '15', 'Add the basil and stand back - there''s a lot of water in basil and it will pop.'),
('5918', '16', 'Let it get crispy, less than a minute. While this is happening, arrange prawns over the citrus salad.'),
('5918', '17', 'Add the orange zest to the basil/garlic/chile mixture in the saute pan. Season with salt and pepper, then spoon basil/garlic/chile mixture over the prawns.'),
('5918', '18', 'Toss the spinach with the citrus vinaigrette and mound on top of the prawns.'),
('5918', '19', 'Serve.'),
('5922', '1', 'Preheat oil to 350F.'),
('5922', '2', 'Place shrimp, green onions and garlic into a large mixing bowl and toss together. Set Aside.'),
('5922', '3', 'Pour water into medium pot and add butter and salt and bring to a boil.'),
('5922', '4', 'Once mixture has come to a boil, add flour and quickly stir with a wooden spoon, until dough forms. Continue to stir over medium heat, for about 3 minutes.'),
('5922', '5', 'Place dough into a stand mixer fixed with a paddle attachment and run on medium speed, allowing steam to escape.'),
('5922', '6', 'Once most of the steam has disappeared add the egg, one at a time, scraping down the sides of the bowl after each addition.'),
('5922', '7', 'Fold pepper into the pate a choux (the doughy/battery mixture).'),
('5922', '8', 'Fold the shrimp mixture into the pate a choux until fully incorporated.'),
('5922', '9', 'Once oil is hot, add tablespoon sized balls of the shrimp mixture into the oil (youll have to do this in batches). make sure not to crowd the pan/fryer.1'),
('5922', '10', 'Fry each fritter for 4 to 6 minutes, flipping halfway if necessary.'),
('5922', '11', 'Drain on a paper towel and season lightly with salt.'),
('5922', '12', 'Serve immediately with spicy honey drizzle.'),
('5923', '1', 'Heat 2 tbsp. oil in a large wide pot over medium-low heat.'),
('5923', '2', 'Add onion and cook, covered, until starting to soften, 5 minutes.'),
('5923', '3', 'Add pasta and more oil if it looks dry, then toast over medium-high heat, turning constantly with tongs, until golden.'),
('5923', '4', 'Add garlic and saffron (if using), tomatoes and tomato paste, sausages, and broth.'),
('5923', '5', 'Boil pasta in soup, uncovered, until noodles are tender, about 5 minutes.'),
('5923', '6', 'Add shrimp and cook just until pink and curled, about 1 minute. Season with salt to taste and stir in parsley.'),
('5924', '1', 'Heat oil in a large saut pan over medium-high heat. Saut onion until golden brown, about 3 minutes. Grind ginger and garlic into a paste. add it and remaining spices and tomatoes to pan. simmer 5 minutes. In a separate pan, saut shrimp 30 seconds.'),
('5924', '2', 'Add sauce and stir continuously on high heat, 2 or 3 minutes, until most of the liquid evaporates.'),
('5924', '3', 'Serve over rice.'),
('5924', '4', 'Garnish with coriander.'),
('5924', '5', 'Heat oil in a large saut pan over medium-high heat. Saut onion until golden brown, about 3 minutes. Grind ginger and garlic into a paste. add it and remaining spices and tomatoes to pan. simmer 5 minutes. In a separate pan, saut shrimp 30 seconds.'),
('5924', '6', 'Add sauce and stir continuously on high heat, 2 or 3 minutes, until most of the liquid evaporates.'),
('5924', '7', 'Serve over rice.'),
('5924', '8', 'Garnish with coriander.'),
('5927', '1', 'In a medium bowl, toss the flour with the baking powder, sugar and salt. In a small bowl, whisk together the egg yolk, water, milk, yogurt and oil. Stir the liquid into the flour mixture with a wooden spoon.'),
('5927', '2', 'Transfer the dough to a lightly floured work surface and knead briefly until smooth. Divide the dough into 4 pieces and shape each piece into an oval disk. Wrap each dough disk in plastic wrap and refrigerate until chilled, about 4 hours or overnight.'),
('5927', '3', 'In a small bowl, stir together 1 tablespoon of the crme frache, 1 tablespoon of the lime juice, 1 tablespoon of the chopped dill and the horseradish and mayonnaise. Fold in the pineapple. Refrigerate until chilled, about 2 hours.'),
('5927', '4', 'Set a large pizza stone in the bottom third of the oven. Preheat the oven to 500 for at least 40 minutes. In a small bowl, combine the remaining 1/4 cup of crme frache with the remaining 1/2 tablespoon of chopped dill and 1/2 tablespoon of the lime juice.'),
('5927', '5', 'On a lightly floured work surface, roll out each piece of dough to a 9-by-7-inch oval. Set the ovals on the pizza stone and bake for about 3 1/2 minutes, or just until golden and puffed.'),
('5927', '6', 'Meanwhile, in a bowl, whisk the oil with the remaining 1 teaspoon of lime juice and season with salt and pepper.'),
('5927', '7', 'Add the greens and toss to coat.'),
('5927', '8', 'Set a hot naan on each of 4 plates and top with the greens. Cover the naans with the pineapple, half of the dill cream and the shrimp. Spoon the remaining dill cream on top and serve at once.'),
('5929', '1', 'Place the lemon grass, garlic, galangal, chili, cilantro, lime juice and zest, green onions, shrimp paste, fish sauce, oil and palm sugar in a foor processor and process.'),
('5929', '2', 'Marinate the shrimp in the paste for at least 10 minutes.'),
('5929', '3', 'Skewer the shrimp.'),
('5929', '4', 'Grill until cooked, about 2-3 minutes per side.'),
('5930', '1', 'Combine 1 cup of the flour with the cayenne, salt, sugar and baking powder in a medium bowl.'),
('5930', '2', 'Add beer all at once and whisk until smooth. Set aside at least 1/2 hour.'),
('5930', '3', 'Heat oil to deep-fry temperature (350/) in a large saucepan. Test oil by sprinkling a few drops of'),
('5930', '4', 'batter and if they rise to the surface, the oil is ready. Toss the shrimps in the flour for dusting and toss to coat evenly, then pat off excess. Drop a few at a time first in the batter then into the hot oil and fry until lightly golden and crispy-- about 2 minutes.'),
('5930', '5', 'Remove with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.'),
('5930', '6', 'Serve immediately with Chipotle Honey Dipping Sauce.'),
('5930', '7', 'In a small saucepan, bring chiles, tomato, water, onion, garlic and salt to a boil and reduce to a simmer. Cook, slowly, covered for 15 minutes, then puree in a blender until smooth transfer to a small bowl and add honey and vinegar.'),
('5930', '8', 'Serve at room temperature as a dipping sauce with shrimps.'),
('5933', '1', 'Combine 2 teaspoons sugar, chili powder, chile powders, and 1/4 teaspoon salt in a shallow dish.'),
('5933', '2', 'Add shrimp to spice mixture. toss well to coat.'),
('5933', '3', 'Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('5933', '4', 'Add 1/2 cup onion, bell pepper, garlic, and ginger to pan. saut 3 minutes.'),
('5933', '5', 'Add remaining 1 1/2 teaspoons sugar and corn to pan. cook 3 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in vinegar. cook 30 seconds.'),
('5933', '6', 'Transfer corn mixture to a bowl. stir in remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/2 cup green onions.'),
('5933', '7', 'Wipe pan with a paper towel.'),
('5933', '8', 'Heat remaining 2 teaspoons oil in pan over medium-high heat.'),
('5933', '9', 'Add shrimp to pan. saut 3 minutes or until done, turning once.'),
('5933', '10', 'Serve with corn mixture.'),
('5934', '1', 'Combine lemon halves, next 3 ingredients, and salted water to cover in a Dutch oven. Bring to a boil. add shrimp, and cook 2 to 3 minutes or just until shrimp turn pink. Plunge shrimp into ice water to stop the cooking process. drain.'),
('5934', '2', 'Peel shrimp, leaving tails on. Devein, if desired.'),
('5934', '3', 'Combine orange juice and next 9 ingredients in a large shallow dish or heavy-duty zip-top plastic bag.'),
('5934', '4', 'Add shrimp, cover or seal, and chill 25 minutes.'),
('5934', '5', 'Drain off liquid.'),
('5934', '6', 'Serve shrimp over lettuce leaves with Louis Sauce.'),
('5934', '7', 'Garnish, if desired.'),
('5936', '1', 'Place yogurt, sour cream, chives, tarragon, garlic, mustard, oil, sugar, salt and pepper in a bowl. Zest lemons over bowl. Juice 1 lemon into bowl.'),
('5936', '2', 'Whisk until smooth.'),
('5936', '3', 'Add shrimp, broccoli, arugula and noodles. Toss to coat and serve with remaining lemon, cut into wedges, if desired.'),
('5936', '4', 'Place yogurt, sour cream, chives, tarragon, garlic, mustard, oil, sugar, salt and pepper in a bowl. Zest lemons over bowl. Juice 1 lemon into bowl.'),
('5936', '5', 'Whisk until smooth.'),
('5936', '6', 'Add shrimp, broccoli, arugula and noodles. Toss to coat and serve with remaining lemon, cut into wedges, if desired.'),
('5937', '1', 'Preheat oven to 450 degrees Fahrenheit.Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil.'),
('5937', '2', 'Cut or break the tough bottoms of the asparagus spears.'),
('5937', '3', 'Spread out the asparagus in one layer on a cookie sheet lined with aluminum foil. Sprinkle olive oil, salt, and pepper evenly on top. Roast in oven for 15 minutes.Toss the cleaned and deveined shrimp in a bowl with salt, pepper, olive oil, and balsamic.'),
('5937', '4', 'Spread evenly in one layer on another cookie sheet lined with aluminum foil. Roast in oven for 8 minutes, until pink and cooked through.Cook the pasta until al dente. Reserve 1/2 cup of the cooking liquid before draining. Toss the pasta immediately with the butter, 1/4 cup of olive oil, lemon juice, and reserved pasta liquid.'),
('5937', '5', 'Add salt and pepper.As soon as the shrimp is cooked, fold into the pasta.'),
('5937', '6', 'Serve immediately alongside the asparagus.'),
('5939', '1', 'Heat the oil and butter in a shallow casserole.'),
('5939', '2', 'Add the shrimp and garlic and saut over high heat about 3 minutes.'),
('5939', '3', 'Add the lemon juice, sherry, paprika, chili pepper, salt, and pepper. Sprinkle with parsley and serve immediately, preferably in the cooking dish.'),
('5939', '4', 'var article'),
('5939', '5', 'Type_27_data = {}.'),
('5939', '6', 'article'),
('5939', '7', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0.'),
('5940', '1', 'Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. When it is very hot, add the curry powder. Cook, stirring, for 2 minutes.'),
('5940', '2', 'Add the onion, scallion, garlic, sweet pepper, Scotch bonnet pepper and black pepper. Cook, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes.'),
('5940', '3', 'Add the tomato sauce or paste and cook 3 minutes more.'),
('5940', '4', 'Add the water and blend well.'),
('5940', '5', 'Add the okra and shrimp. Reduce the heat to medium, cover and cook until the shrimp are just cooked through, about 5 minutes. It is best served hot, straight out of the pan.'),
('5940', '6', 'var article'),
('5940', '7', 'Type_27_data = {}.'),
('5940', '8', 'article'),
('5940', '9', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0.'),
('5942', '1', 'Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl. set aside.'),
('5942', '2', 'Place a large nonstick skillet coated with cooking spray over medium heat until hot.'),
('5942', '3', 'Add shrimp and seasoning. saut 2 minutes.'),
('5942', '4', 'Add yogurt spread mixture, and cook 3 minutes or until shrimp are done. Spoon shrimp and liquid into individual serving bowls, and sprinkle with parsley.'),
('5944', '1', 'Prepare Gruy&egrave.re Grits. set aside, and keep warm.'),
('5944', '2', 'While grits are cooking, heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. add bell pepper, onion, and garlic, and saut&eacute. 2 minutes to soften.'),
('5944', '3', 'Add sausage, and cook 6 to 7 minutes or until browned, stirring often.'),
('5944', '4', 'Add wine, and cook until almost all liquid has evaporated.'),
('5944', '5', 'Sprinkle flour over mixture in skillet, and cook 3 minutes, stirring constantly. (Flour will start to brown.) Gradually whisk in chicken broth and cream. add bay leaves and Creole seasoning.'),
('5944', '6', 'Bring mixture to a simmer, and cook, uncovered, 7 minutes or until thick, stirring often. ('),
('5944', '7', 'Mixture may be cooked to this point, and then covered and kept warm until serving time.)'),
('5944', '8', 'Just before serving, add shrimp to sauce, and cook 3 to 4 minutes or until shrimp turn pink, stirring often.'),
('5944', '9', 'Remove and discard bay leaves, and stir in parsley. Spoon shrimp and sauce over Gruy&egrave.re Grits, and serve immediately.'),
('5945', '1', 'Combine the first 3 ingredients in a shallow baking dish. toss to combine. Weigh or lightly spoon rice flour and all-purpose flour into dry measuring cups. level with a knife.'),
('5945', '2', 'Combine flours and baking soda in a large bowl, stirring with a whisk. Gradually add beer, stirring with a whisk until smooth.'),
('5945', '3', 'Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('5945', '4', 'Add 3 tablespoons oil to pan. swirl to coat. Dip half of shrimp in batter. shake off excess. Dredge shrimp lightly in panko mixture.'),
('5945', '5', 'Place shrimp in a single layer in pan, and cook for 2 1/2 minutes on each side or until golden brown.'),
('5945', '6', 'Remove shrimp from pan. drain on paper towels. Repeat procedure with the remaining oil, shrimp, batter, and panko mixture.'),
('5946', '1', 'Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl. stir well with a whisk.'),
('5946', '2', 'Add shrimp. toss to coat.'),
('5946', '3', 'Place in an 8-inch square baking dish. Cover and marinate 4 hours.'),
('5946', '4', 'Microwave, uncovered, at HIGH 6 minutes or until shrimp are done, stirring after 3 minutes.'),
('5948', '1', 'Prepare Grits: Bring 7 cups water to a boil in a 4-qt. saucepan over medium-high heat. Slowly whisk in grits. reduce heat to medium, and cook, whisking constantly, 5 minutes. Cover, reduce heat to low, and cook, stirring occasionally, 1 hour or until tender. Fold in cheese and 1/4 cup butter.'),
('5948', '2', 'Prepare Shrimp Sauce: Peel shrimp. devein, if desired.'),
('5948', '3', 'Cook bacon in a large skillet over medium-high heat, stirring often, 4 to 5 minutes or until crisp. remove bacon, and drain on paper towels, reserving 2 Tbsp. drippings in skillet.'),
('5948', '4', 'Melt 6 Tbsp. butter in hot drippings in skillet. Reduce heat.'),
('5948', '5', 'Add onion, poblano pepper, and garlic. saut 2 minutes or until onion is translucent.'),
('5948', '6', 'Add shrimp. cook, stirring often, 1 to 2 minutes.'),
('5948', '7', 'Add salt and next 2 ingredients. toss to coat.'),
('5948', '8', 'Sprinkle flour over shrimp mixture. toss.'),
('5948', '9', 'Add broth and next 2 ingredients. Cook just until shrimp turn pink, stirring to loosen particles from skillet. Stir in bacon and parsley.'),
('5948', '10', 'Serve over grits with green onion.'),
('5949', '1', 'Stir bulgur, 1 1/2 cups water, 1/2 cup lemon juice, and 1/3 cup oil in large bowl.'),
('5949', '2', 'Let stand until bulgur is tender and most liquid is absorbed, about 2 hours.'),
('5949', '3', 'Meanwhile, whisk together remaining 2 tablespoons lemon juice, 2 tablespoons oil, 3 tablespoons mint, and 1/2 teaspoon salt in medium bowl.'),
('5949', '4', 'Mix in shrimp. Marinate 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.'),
('5949', '5', 'Drain off any excess liquid from bulgur.'),
('5949', '6', 'Mix in tomatoes, arugula, feta, green onions, garlic, remaining 3 tablespoons mint, and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt. Season salad to taste with pepper.'),
('5949', '7', 'Mound salad in large shallow bowl or on individual plates. Spoon shrimp and dressing over and serve.'),
('5949', '8', '*Also called cracked wheat. available at supermarkets, specialty foods stores, and natural foods stores.'),
('5950', '1', 'Soak wooden skewers in water 30 minutes.'),
('5950', '2', 'If frozen, thaw shrimp according to package directions. Peel shrimp, leaving tails on. devein, if desired.'),
('5950', '3', 'Place shrimp in a medium bowl.'),
('5950', '4', 'Stir together chili with lime seasoning, ground mustard, and garlic powder in a small bowl. Sprinkle mixture over shrimp, tossing to coat.'),
('5950', '5', 'Grate rind from 1 lime, and add to shrimp mixture in bowl.'),
('5950', '6', 'Cut lime in half, and squeeze juice into bowl. Stir in olive oil. Thread 4 to 5 shrimp onto each skewer, and place skewers on a plate. Cover and chill.'),
('5950', '7', 'Preheat grill to 300 to 350 (medium).'),
('5950', '8', 'Prepare Seasoned White Beans and Rice.'),
('5950', '9', 'Meanwhile, grill shrimp skewers, covered with grill lid, over 300 to 350 (medium) heat 3 to 4 minutes on each side or just until shrimp turn pink. Spoon Seasoned White Beans and Rice onto a serving platter, and top with shrimp skewers.'),
('5950', '10', 'Garnish, if desired.'),
('5950', '11', 'Note: For testing purposes only, we used McCormick Chili With Lime Seasoning.'),
('5951', '1', '1 In a blender, puree the first 8 ingredients until they form a paste.'),
('5951', '2', '2 In a large bowl, toss your protein with the marinade. Chill for at least 4 hours or overnight.'),
('5951', '3', '3 When ready to cook, heat the grill and shake any excess marinade from the protein. Grill 9 minutes for chops, 6 to 8 minutes a side on a covered grill for chicken, or 4 minutes a side for shrimp.'),
('5951', '4', 'Serve.'),
('5952', '1', 'Snip shells of shrimp with scissors down middle of back, leaving tail and first segment of shell intact. Make an incision along length of back where shells are cut and devein, leaving shells in place. (Shells will prevent shrimp from becoming tough on outside when grilled.) Toss shrimp with oil, garlic, and 1/2 teaspoon salt and marinate at cool room temperature 15 minutes.'),
('5952', '2', 'While shrimp marinate, prepare grill for cooking. If using a charcoal grill, open vents on bottom of grill, then light charcoal. Charcoal fire is medium-hot when you can hold your hand 5 inches above rack for 3 to 4 seconds. If using a gas grill, preheat burners on high, covered, 10 minutes, then reduce heat to moderately high.'),
('5952', '3', 'Heat butter, chili powder, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, and remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt in a small heavy saucepan over moderately low heat, stirring, until butter is melted, then remove from heat and stir in lemon juice.'),
('5952', '4', 'Thread 4 or 5 shrimp onto each skewer and grill, covered only if using a gas grill, turning over once, until just cooked through, 3 to 4 minutes total. Push shrimp off skewers into a bowl, then pour butter mixture over them and toss to combine well.'),
('5953', '1', 'Rinse the shrimp under cold running water, then blot them dry with paper  towels.'),
('5953', '2', 'Place the chile powder, garlic salt, coriander, oregano, cumin, and pepper in a mixing bowl and whisk to mix.'),
('5953', '3', 'Add the shrimp and toss to coat. Stir in the olive oil.'),
('5953', '4', 'Let the shrimp marinate in the refrigerator, covered, for 30 minutes to 1 hour.'),
('5953', '5', 'Cook the shrimp, following the instructions below for any of the grills, until just cooked through. When done the shrimp will turn pinkish white and will feel firm to the touch.'),
('5953', '6', 'Spoon the Avocado and Corn Salsa into 4 large martini glasses or serving bowls. Drape 4 of the hot shrimp over the edge of each glass or bowl and serve at once. Or for a cold shrimp cocktail, let the cooked shrimp cool to room temperature. Refrigerate the shrimp, covered, until they are chilled before serving them with the salsa. The cooked shrimp can be refrigerated for up to 2 days.'),
('5954', '1', 'To prepare shrimp, combine first 3 ingredients in a large zip-top plastic bag.'),
('5954', '2', 'Add shrimp to bag. seal. Marinate in refrigerator for 2 hours, turning bag occasionally.'),
('5954', '3', 'Prepare grill to medium-high heat.'),
('5954', '4', 'Remove shrimp from bag. Sprinkle shrimp with 1/4 teaspoon salt.'),
('5954', '5', 'Place shrimp on grill rack coated with cooking spray. grill 3 minutes on each side or until shrimp are done.'),
('5954', '6', 'Drizzle 2 tablespoons juice over shrimp. keep warm.'),
('5954', '7', 'To prepare chutney, combine onion and remaining ingredients except the cilantro sprigs in a food processor. process until smooth.'),
('5954', '8', 'Serve with shrimp.'),
('5954', '9', 'Garnish with cilantro sprigs, if desired.'),
('5955', '1', 'If using bamboo skewers, soak skewers in water at least 30 minutes. Prepare outdoor grill for direct grilling on medium-high.In blender, puree cilantro, sour cream, mayonnaise, 2 tablespoons lemon juice, vinegar, 1/4 teaspoon salt, and 1/2 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper. set dressing aside.In large bowl, combine shrimp, oil, coriander, remaining 2 tablespoons lemon juice, 1/8 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper, tossing until well coated.Thread shrimp, 1/2 inch apart, on skewers. Grill 3 to 4 minutes or until shrimp just turn opaque, turning over once.'),
('5955', '2', 'Transfer to plate.In another large bowl, toss lettuce with half of dressing until well coated. Divide among 4 serving plates. In same bowl, toss tomatoes and apple with half of remaining dressing until well coated. place on lettuce with shrimp.'),
('5955', '3', 'Drizzle with remaining dressing.'),
('5956', '1', 'Heat grill. Fold four 18-inch-long pieces of foil in half. unfold and coat inside with cooking spray.'),
('5956', '2', 'Place 2 cups spinach in center of 1 half of each piece of foil.'),
('5956', '3', 'Combine couscous with 1/4 cup water. divide evenly among packets, placing on top of spinach.'),
('5956', '4', 'Combine shrimp, 1/4 cup cilantro, oil and 1/2 tsp salt in a bowl. Divide shrimp evenly among packets, placing next to couscous. Fold foil to close and crimp edges to seal. place on grill. close lid. cook until packets are fully puffed, 10 minutes.'),
('5956', '5', 'Combine remaining 1/4 cup cilantro with remaining 1/4 tsp salt, mango, avocado, tomato, onion, jalapeo and lime juice in a bowl. Carefully cut foil to open. stir contents. garnish with salsa before serving.'),
('5956', '6', 'Heat grill. Fold four 18-inch-long pieces of foil in half. unfold and coat inside with cooking spray.'),
('5956', '7', 'Place 2 cups spinach in center of 1 half of each piece of foil.'),
('5956', '8', 'Combine couscous with 1/4 cup water. divide evenly among packets, placing on top of spinach.'),
('5956', '9', 'Combine shrimp, 1/4 cup cilantro, oil and 1/2 tsp salt in a bowl. Divide shrimp evenly among packets, placing next to couscous. Fold foil to close and crimp edges to seal. place on grill. close lid. cook until packets are fully puffed, 10 minutes.'),
('5956', '10', 'Combine remaining 1/4 cup cilantro with remaining 1/4 tsp salt, mango, avocado, tomato, onion, jalapeo and lime juice in a bowl. Carefully cut foil to open. stir contents. garnish with salsa before serving.'),
('5958', '1', 'Heat oil in a medium saute pan over high heat. Saute garlic until browned, about 2 minutes.'),
('5958', '2', 'Add shrimp and chiles. saute until shrimp are cooked through, about 4 minutes.'),
('5958', '3', 'Add brandy and cook 1 minute more.'),
('5958', '4', 'Remove from heat.'),
('5958', '5', 'Transfer to a platter or divide equally among 8 small plates. Sprinkle with parsley, add salt to taste and serve.'),
('5959', '1', 'In a medium bowl, stir together garlic and ginger.'),
('5959', '2', 'Transfer half of the mixture to a large bowl and stir in 2 tablespoons oil.'),
('5959', '3', 'Add the shrimp, toss until evenly coated, and then cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes. Cover remaining garlic-ginger mixture and refrigerate.'),
('5961', '1', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Coat pan with cooking spray.'),
('5961', '2', 'Add 1/2 cup onions. coat onions with cooking spray. Cook 1 minute, stirring occasionally.'),
('5961', '3', 'Add shrimp and chili powder. cook 4 minutes or until desired degree of doneness, stirring occasionally.'),
('5961', '4', 'Remove from heat.'),
('5961', '5', 'Add lime juice, butter, and salt, and stir until butter melts. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup onions.'),
('5962', '1', 'Spread salt in 13x9x2-inch baking dish.Arrange shrimp in single layer atop salt.'),
('5962', '2', 'Preheat oven to 500F. Boil wine,lemon juice, and garlic in saucepan overmedium-high heat until liquid is reducedto 1 tablespoon, about 10 minutes.'),
('5962', '3', 'Removefrom heat.'),
('5962', '4', 'Add a few pieces of butter.whisk until creamy. Return pan to lowheat.'),
('5962', '5', 'Add a few more pieces of butter.whisk until smooth (do not let mixture boil).Continue whisking in butter, a few piecesat a time. Stir in parsley. season with saltand pepper.'),
('5962', '6', 'Let stand while shrimp cook.'),
('5962', '7', 'Roast shrimp on salt until just opaquein center and shells are pink, 6 to 7 minutes.'),
('5962', '8', 'Transfer sauce to bowl. nestle in salt.'),
('5963', '1', 'Blend cream cheese, grape leaves, and lemon juice in mini processor until grape leaves are minced and mixture is blended. Season spread to taste with salt and pepper. Can be made 1 day ahead.'),
('5963', '2', 'Transfer spread to small bowl. Cover and refrigerate. Bring spread to room temperature before using.'),
('5964', '1', 'Preheat oven to 400F. Line a baking sheet (with sides) with parchment paper. Finely grate the zest of 1 orange. set aside. Using a sharp knife, peel both oranges, removing all the bitter white pith. Thinly slice the oranges crosswise, then cut the slices into quarters.'),
('5964', '2', 'Spread the orange slices on the prepared baking sheet and sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon salt. Roast until the oranges are slightly dry, about 12 minutes.Meanwhile, toss shrimp with oil, curry powder, pepper, the orange zest and the remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt in a large bowl.'),
('5964', '3', 'Transfer the shrimp to the baking sheet with the oranges and roast until pink and curled, about 6 minutes. Divide the oranges and the shrimp among 4 plates and serve.'),
('5965', '1', 'Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl. Grill shrimp until cooked through, about 3 minutes per side.'),
('5965', '2', 'Serve with dipping sauce on the side.'),
('5965', '3', 'Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl. Grill shrimp until cooked through, about 3 minutes per side.'),
('5965', '4', 'Serve with dipping sauce on the side.'),
('5966', '1', 'Peel shrimp, and devein, if desired. set aside.'),
('5966', '2', 'Combine cornstarch and salt in a large zip-top plastic bag.'),
('5966', '3', 'Whisk together egg whites and peppers in a shallow dish.'),
('5966', '4', 'Combine cornmeal and cumin in a shallow dish.'),
('5966', '5', 'Place shrimp in bag with cornstarch mixture. shake to coat well. Dip in egg white mixture, and roll in cornmeal mixture. Fry shrimp, in batches, in 2 inches hot oil (35'),
('5966', '6', 'until golden.'),
('5966', '7', 'Serve with Red Pepper-Chipotle Dipping Sauce, and garnish, if desired.'),
('5968', '1', 'Cook the noodles:    Bring a medium potful of water to a rolling boil.'),
('5968', '2', 'Add the rice vermicelli and, stirring often, cook them until the strands are soft and white, but still resilient, 3 to 5 minutes. Don''t be tempted to undercook them, as they must be fully cooked to absorb the flavors of the dish. Rinse them in a colander under cold water just until they''re cool and the water runs clear.'),
('5968', '3', 'Let the noodles drain in the colander for 30 minutes, and then set them aside for up to 2 hours, unrefrigerated.    Cook the shrimp:    In a large skillet, heat the oil over high heat.'),
('5968', '4', 'Add the shallots and garlic, quickly stirring until fragrant, about 30 seconds.'),
('5968', '5', 'Add the shrimp and lemongrass. stir-fry for about 2 minutes.'),
('5968', '6', 'Add the mushrooms and sprinkle with the fish sauce, sugar, and a little salt. Stir-fry until the shrimp is cooked and the mushrooms are wilted, another 2 to 3 minutes.'),
('5968', '7', 'Remove from the heat.    Assemble the salads:    Divide the lettuce, bean sprouts, cucumber, mint, and basil among four large soup or pasta bowls. Fluff the noodles with your fingers and divide them among the prepared salad bowls.'),
('5968', '8', 'Put the shrimp topping on the noodles and garnish each bowl with the peanuts and cilantro. Pass the nuoc cham at the table. each diner should drizzle about 3 Tbs. over the salad and then toss the salad in the bowl a few times with two forks or chopsticks before eating.'),
('5968', '9', 'Photo: Ben Fink'),
('5968', '10', 'Rate this Recipe and View Reviews'),
('5969', '1', 'Preheat oven to 375F with rack in middle.'),
('5969', '2', 'Cook onion and garlic in oil with 1/4 teaspoon salt in a 4-quart heavy saucepan over medium heat until softened, about 5 minutes. Stir in spices and cook, stirring, 30 seconds.'),
('5969', '3', 'Add chopped tomatoes with juice and sugar and simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened, about 20 minutes.'),
('5969', '4', 'Remove from heat.'),
('5969', '5', 'Season shrimp with 1/8 teaspoon salt, then stir into tomato sauce.'),
('5969', '6', 'Transfer to a 2-quart shallow baking dish and top with feta.'),
('5969', '7', 'Bake until just cooked through, 18 to 20 minutes.'),
('5969', '8', 'Serve sprinkled with dill.'),
