('5973', '9', 'Saute ginger and garlic about 45 seconds.'),
('5973', '10', 'Add shrimp and chile paste, tossing to cook evenly, about 3 minutes.'),
('5973', '11', 'Add lemon juice and stir.'),
('5973', '12', 'Serve raita with shrimp. garnish with chives.Red Mountain Spa, St. George, UT'),
('5975', '1', 'Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('5975', '2', 'Add thyme, capers, and garlic. saut 1 minute.'),
('5975', '3', 'Add shrimp and lemon juice. saut 4 minutes or until shrimp are done.'),
('5975', '4', 'Microwave rice according to package directions.'),
('5975', '5', 'Serve shrimp mixture over rice.'),
('5975', '6', 'Serve with: Greek-Style Green Beans'),
('5976', '1', 'Combine everything in a bowl and let marinate in the refrigerator for 20 minutes or up to 1 hour.'),
('5976', '2', 'Drain and blot shrimp dry before grilling over medium high heat just until barely cooked through, one to two minutes per side.'),
('5976', '3', 'Serve hot or refrigerate until ready to serve.'),
('5980', '1', 'Place first 3 ingredients in a blender. process until smooth.'),
('5980', '2', 'Heat a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Coat pan with cooking spray. add shrimp. Coat shrimp with cooking spray. sprinkle with cumin and salt. Saut 4 minutes or until shrimp are done, stirring frequently.'),
('5980', '3', 'Transfer shrimp to a serving platter. Reduce heat to medium, add half-and-half mixture to pan, and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.'),
('5980', '4', 'Pour sauce over shrimp. sprinkle with cilantro.'),
('5980', '5', 'Serve over linguine, if desired.'),
('5981', '1', 'Using a sharp knife, peel the oranges, removing all of the bitter white pith. Working over a strainer set over a medium bowl, cut between the membranes to release the orange sections into the strainer. Squeeze the juice from the membranes into the bowl through the strainer.'),
('5981', '2', 'Whisk 1 teaspoon of the hot sauce into the strained juice with 1 tablespoon of the oil and the mint. Season with salt and pepper. add the shrimp and toss.'),
('5981', '3', 'In another bowl, combine the lime juice with the remaining 1/4 cup of oil and 1 teaspoon of hot sauce.'),
('5981', '4', 'Add the tomatoes, onion, cilantro and oregano and the orange sections. Season lightly with salt.'),
('5981', '5', 'Light a grill or heat a grill pan. Grill the shrimp over high heat for about 4 minutes, turning once or twice until lightly charred and cooked through.'),
('5981', '6', 'Transfer the shrimp to plates. Gently fold the avocados into the orange salad and serve alongside the shrimp.'),
('5982', '1', 'In a mini food processor, blend the egg white, salt, wine, and cornstarch until thick and smooth, about 2 minute. Or mix the ingredients by hand, smoothing lumps with your fingers and beating with a fork to thicken slightly.    With your hands, toss the chicken or fish with the marinade to evenly coat and separate the pieces. Cover with plastic and refrigerate for 30 minutes or overnight.    In a wok or stir-fry pan, bring the water to a steaming, near simmer, or bring the oil to the slow-fry stage, 275F on a deep-fry thermometer. Next to the stove, set a plate big enough to hold the fish or chicken in a single layer. Have a large Chinese mesh skimmer at hand.    Toss the chicken or fish once more and slide it into the hot water or oil, leaving any excess marinade behind. Stir gently with chopsticks to separate the pieces. Watch carefully to see when the outside turns 95% white, 5 to 10 seconds for shreds or tiny cubes, 30 to 45 seconds for larger nuggets. Scoop out the food promptly with the mesh spoon and quickly spread it on the plate.'),
('5982', '2', 'Rate this Recipe and View Reviews'),
('5984', '1', 'Bring the water to a boil and stir in the sugar.When the sugar water turns golden add the walnuts and boil for 2 minutes.Strain the walnuts and set them on parchment paper to cool.'),
('5984', '2', 'Heat the oil in a pan.Dip the shrimp into the egg and then into the corn starch.Fry the shrimp in the oil until golden brown'),
('5984', '3', 'Mix the mayonnaise, honey, sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice in a bowl.'),
('5984', '4', 'Add the shrimp and toss to coat.'),
('5984', '5', 'Serve the shrimp garnished with the walnuts.'),
('5985', '1', 'Heat the oil in a pan.'),
('5985', '2', 'Add the shallots and saute until tender, about 3-5 minutes.'),
('5985', '3', 'Add the garlic, jalapeo and cumin and saute until fragrant, about 1 minute.'),
('5985', '4', 'Add the shrimp, tequila and cook until the shrimp are pink, about 1-3 minutes per side.'),
('5985', '5', 'Remove the shrimp and set aside.Simmer the sauce to reduce to the desired amount.'),
('5985', '6', 'Remove from the heat and add the shrimp, lime juice, cilantro and salt and pepper.'),
('5986', '1', 'Heat the oil in a pan.'),
('5986', '2', 'Add the shrimp and saute until cooked, about 2-3 minutes per side and set aside.'),
('5986', '3', 'Add the garlic and ginger and saute until fragrant, about a minute.'),
('5986', '4', 'Add the orange juice, orange zest, soy sauce, rice wine, honey and chili sauce, deglaze the pan and simmer to reduce to a sauce like consistency.'),
('5986', '5', 'Remove from heat and mix in the shrimp and cilantro.'),
('5987', '1', 'Marinate the shrimp in the sweet chili sauce, lemon juice, lemon zest, kaffir lime leaves, chili sauce, fish sauce, garlic and sugar for 10 or more minutes.'),
('5987', '2', 'Heat a pan over medium heat.'),
('5987', '3', 'Add the shrimp along with the marinade and the coconut milk and simmer until the shrimp are cooked, about 2-3 minutes.'),
('5987', '4', 'Remove from heat and mix in the cilantro.'),
('5988', '1', 'Heat your gas grill at high heat.Skewer the shrimp on metal or wooden skewers (be sure to soak wooden skewers in water ahead of time).'),
('5988', '2', 'Drizzle olive oil on both sides of the shrimp. Salt and pepper generously.'),
('5988', '3', 'Place the shrimp on the grill for 1-2 minutes on each side.'),
('5988', '4', 'Add the lemon to the grill as well.Take the shrimp and lemon off the grill and squeeze the lemon over the shrimp before serving.'),
('5991', '1', 'Heat the broiler or prepare a grill fire. In a large bowl, combine the coriander, mint, curry powder, garlic, ginger, peppercorns, and salt. Toss the shrimp with the rub and then thread them onto skewers. Broil or grill until just opaque and cooked through, 5 to 6 minutes, turning once.'),
('5993', '1', 'Mix the Kung Pao sauce ingredients and set aside.'),
('5993', '2', 'Heat up a wok and add the cooking oil until the oil is very hot.'),
('5993', '3', 'Add the ginger and do a few quick stirs.'),
('5993', '4', 'Addthe onion,green pepper, and dried red chilies. Stir-fry until you smell the spicy aromas from the dried red chilies.'),
('5993', '5', 'Add in the shrimp and roasted peanuts and keep stirring.When the shrimp are almost cooked, add the Kung Pao sauce into the wok, keep stirring until the sauce thickens.'),
('5993', '6', 'Add the chopped scallions, do a few quick stirs, dish out and serve hot.'),
('5994', '1', 'Whisk together the vinegar, sugar, and salt.'),
('5994', '2', 'Place the cucumber, red pepper, and lemon zest in a medium mixing bowl.'),
('5994', '3', 'Pour the dressing over the vegetables. Toss gently to coat. Chill the vegetables and let stand for 1 hour before serving.'),
('5994', '4', 'For the puree: In a sauce pot, combine the vinegar, sugar, ginger, and lemon juice. Simmer the mixture over medium-low heat until big bubbles start to form and it becomes a light syrup. Reduce until thickened.'),
('5994', '5', 'Remove the pot from the heat.'),
('5994', '6', 'Meanwhile, in a large pot, combine the parsnips, potatoes, and chicken stock, and bring to a boil. Cook until both the parsnips and potatoes are fork tender.'),
('5994', '7', 'Drain the parsnips and potatoes, and mash with the heavy cream, butter, and ginger syrup until smooth. Season the parsnip-potato mash with salt, to taste.'),
('5994', '8', 'Heat a large saute pan over medium-high heat and add the olive oil, garlic, and shrimp. Cook the shrimp for about 3 minutes, or until cooked through. On a warmed serving platter, make a bed of parsnip puree, top with the shrimp, then top the shrimp with the pickled vegetables and some of the juice.'),
('5997', '1', 'If using regular yogurt, place it in a strainer lined with paper towel and set the strainer over a bowl.'),
('5997', '2', 'Let the yogurt drain and thicken for 20 minutes.In a bowl, stir together the thickened or Greek-style yogurt, mayonnaise, celery, scallion and lemon juice. Fold in the lobster meat and season, to taste, with salt and pepper. Chill until ready to use. Just before serving, open the hot dog buns and brush the inside with olive oil.'),
('5997', '3', 'Heat a grill pan over moderately high heat and grill the bread, cut side down, until toasted, about 3 minutes. Fill each with 3/4 cup of the lobster mixture and serve immediately.'),
('6000', '1', 'Whisk tamarind concentrate into lime juice in a small bowl until dissolved. Stir in remaining sauce ingredients and chill, covered.'),
('6001', '1', 'In a blender, puree the 1/3 cup of basil leaves with the olive oil until smooth. Season the oil with salt and black pepper.'),
('6001', '2', 'Light a grill or preheat a grill pan. In a small bowl, mix the sweet smoked paprika with the pure ancho chile powder, light brown sugar, cumin, coriander, cayenne pepper, 1/2 teaspoon of salt and 1/4 teaspoon of black pepper.'),
('6001', '3', 'Brush the shrimp with the canola oil and season all over with the spice mixture. Grill the shrimp over moderately high heat, turning once, until they are lightly charred and cooked through, about 4 minutes total.'),
('6001', '4', 'Arrange the tomato and onion slices on a platter and drizzle with the basil oil. Top with the shrimp, garnish with the remaining basil leaves and serve.'),
('6002', '1', 'In a medium bowl, combine the orange juice with the garlic, adobo sauce and 1 tablespoon of the lime juice.'),
('6002', '2', 'Add the shrimp, season with salt and pepper. let sit at room temperature for 10 minutes.'),
('6002', '3', 'Preheat a grill pan. Thread the onion slices on skewers to hold them together.'),
('6002', '4', 'Brush the onions with some of the olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Grill the slices over high heat, turning once, until softened and charred, about 3 minutes per side.'),
('6002', '5', 'Let cool slightly, then coarsely chop the onions and transfer them to a medium bowl.'),
('6002', '6', 'Add the sliced oranges, chipotles, cilantro and the remaining 1 tablespoon lime juice. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('6002', '7', 'Drain and thread the shrimp onto 6 metal skewers.'),
('6002', '8', 'Brush lightly with the remaining olive oil and grill over moderately high heat, turning occasionally, until charred in spots, about 5 minutes.'),
('6002', '9', 'Serve the shrimp with the onion and orange salad.'),
('6004', '1', 'Stir rice vinegar, olive oil, lemon juice, lemon slices, onion slices, garlic cloves, bay leaves, celery seeds, mustard seeds, coarse kosher salt, and black pepper in large bowl until salt dissolves. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and chill.'),
('6006', '1', 'Stir together ingredients, 1/8 teaspoon salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.'),
('6007', '1', 'Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil in a medium saucepan. gradually whisk in grits. Reduce heat, and simmer, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes or until thickened.'),
('6007', '2', 'Add Cheddar cheese and next 4 ingredients. Keep warm.'),
('6007', '3', 'Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp. remove bacon, and drain on paper towels, reserving 1 tablespoon drippings in skillet. Crumble bacon, and set aside.'),
('6007', '4', 'Sprinkle shrimp with pepper and salt. dredge in flour.'),
('6007', '5', 'Saut mushrooms in hot drippings in skillet 5 minutes or until tender.'),
('6007', '6', 'Add green onions, and saut 2 minutes.'),
('6007', '7', 'Add shrimp and garlic, and saut 2 minutes or until shrimp are lightly brown. Stir in chicken broth, lemon juice, and hot sauce, and cook 2 more minutes, stirring to loosen particles from bottom of skillet.'),
('6007', '8', 'Serve shrimp mixture over hot cheese grits. Top with crumbled bacon. serve with lemon wedges.'),
('6008', '1', 'Marinate the shrimp in the orange juice and zest, chipotles, oil and cilantro for 15+ minutes.'),
('6008', '2', 'Remove the shrimp from the marinade and season with salt and pepper.Skewer the shrimp and grill or fry in a pan for 1-3 minutes per side.'),
('6009', '1', 'Inspiration can come from a variety of sources. It can strike when I''m browsing the Farmers Market, or flipping through a cooking magazine, or falling asleep at night, dreaming of the things I want to eat the next day. It''s an elusive and wonderful thing, inspiration, and when it strikes, you have to seize on it.The September 2010 issue of "Food & Wine" magazine takes on Southern cooking in a modern and delightful way. I''ve been whipping up several recipes inspired by their articles, including this one for Smoky Shrimp with Grits.Last weekend, bored with the same old lunch, I made this shrimp dish, a warm hearty meal, perfect for the start of football season (Kuzak is a massive UMich fan). I always keep raw, frozen shrimp in my freezer. Lately, I''ve been enjoying pink Gulf Coast shrimp (while I can). The shrimp is sauteed with garlic and smoked paprika, which turns into a lovely red-tinged sauce when reduced with wine, and served over grits with roasted heirloom cherry tomatoes and goat cheese. I served it with a plate of lovely mixed greens.This dish would be great for lunch or dinner (it cooks up in a jiffy), and pairs best with a rich California Chardonnay. Enjoy!Smoky Shrimp and Grits with Roasted Cherry Tomatoes and Goat Cheese'),
('6009', '2', 'Adapted from "Food & Wine" Sept. 2010'),
('6009', '3', 'Serves 4 people'),
('6009', '4', 'Cooking time: 30 minutes'),
('6009', '5', 'Print Recipe Ingredients1 lb medium shrimp, shelled and deveined 1/2 teaspoon smoked paprika (pimenton)2 large garlic cloves, peeled and thinly sliced1/4 cup dry white wine2 tablespoons olive oilsalt & peppergrits:3/4 cup quick-cooking gritssalt & pepper2 cups cherry tomatoes, halved1 tablespoons olive oil1/4 cup fresh goat cheese (chevre)Directions'),
('6009', '6', 'Preheat oven to 425 degrees.'),
('6009', '7', 'Place the cherry tomatoes in a roasting pan.'),
('6009', '8', 'Drizzle with the olive oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Roast in the oven until soft and bubbling (about 20 minutes).'),
('6009', '9', 'Remove and set aside.Meanwhile, to make the grits, in a medium saucepan, bring 3 cups of water to a boil. Gradually add the grits and add a generous pinch of salt. Cover and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until the grits are thick and porridge-like (about 7 minutes). Stir in the roasted cherry tomatoes and goat cheese. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Cover the grits and keep them warm.In a large skillet, heat the olive oil with the garlic over high heat until fragrant (about 30 seconds).'),
('6009', '10', 'Add the shrimp and paprika, season with salt and pepper and cook until the shrimp are opaque (about 2 minutes).'),
('6009', '11', 'Add the white wine and cook until the shrimp are white throughout and the garlic-paprika sauce is slightly reduced.Spoon the grits into bowls and top with the shrimp and sauce. Enjoy!Source for Ingredientsfrozen wild caught Gulf shrimp, smoked paprika, and organic grits from Whole Foodsorganic garlic and Soledad Farms goat cheese from Hollywood Farmers Marketorganic heirloom cherry tomatoes from Trader Joe''s');